SELECT p.first_name, p.last_name, p.email, c.description
             FROM patients p

             WHERE c.id = '108e5d55-e704-b869-eee7-4e2525abcca5';

question: What is the most promising procedure for a patient with Animal dander (substance)?
answers:
SELECT p.description 
             FROM procedures p 
             JOIN encounters e ON p.encounter = e.id 
             JOIN allergies a ON e.id = a.encounter 
             WHERE a.description=' Animal dander (substance)' 
             ORDER BY p.priority DESC 
             LIMIT 1;

            [Q]: 'What is the most promising procedure for a patient with Animal dander (substance) and age 30-40?'
            [SQL]: 
             SELECT p.description 
             FROM procedures p 
             JOIN encounters e ON p.encounter = e.id 
             JOIN allergies a ON e.id = a.encounter 
             WHERE a.description=' Animal dander (substance)' 
             AND e.patient_age BETWEEN 30 AND 40 
             ORDER BY p.priority DESC 
             LIMIT 1;

question: In what climate does Allergy to substance (finding) occur in most?
answers:
SELECT c.description AS climate, COUNT(*) AS count 
             FROM findings f 
             JOIN substances s ON f.substance = s.id 
             JOIN encounters e ON f.encounter = e.id 
             JOIN climates c ON e.climate = c.id 
             WHERE s.description='Allergy to substance (finding)' 
             GROUP BY c.description 
             ORDER BY count DESC;

            [Q]: 'What is the most common substance causing Allergy to substance (finding)?'
            [SQL]: 
             SELECT s.description AS substance, COUNT(*) AS count 
             FROM findings f 
             JOIN substances s ON f.substance = s.id 
             WHERE f.description='Allergy to substance (finding)' 
             GROUP BY s.description 
             ORDER BY count DESC;

            [Q]: 'What is the most common climate where Allergy to substance (finding) occurs?'
            [SQL]: 
             SELECT c.description AS climate, COUNT(*) AS count 
             FROM findings f
